<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="38" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="38">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="38">
This monotypic genus includes a single grass-living species, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Sphaeropothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sphaeropothrips vittipennis" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittipennis">Sphaeropothrips vittipennis</taxonomicName>
(Bagnall) that was recorded from Iran by 
<bibRefCitation author="Minaei, K" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Entomological Society of Iran" pageId="13" pageNumber="40" pagination="29 - 36" title="The Thrips genus-group (Thysanoptera: Thripidae) in Iran." volume="27" year="2007">Minaei et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. It is included in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Thrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Thrips</taxonomicName>
genus-group (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound, LA" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica Scandinavica" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" pagination="153 - 17" title="Phylogenetic relationships between some genera of Thripidae (Thysanoptera)." volume="15" year="1981 a">Mound and Palmer 1981a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
